<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-04-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-04-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="760" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d760">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Andrade</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-04-26"><hi rend="italic">April 26,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 6.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 22d instant, in which you advise the
                            Department that you have been informed by the minister of foreign
                            relations at Caracas that the report of the hostile attitude of England,
                            because of the Cuyuni incident, appears to be without foundation.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>